1. Download Tomcatï¼š
Tomcat Website
https://tomcat.apache.org/
Choose the version you want from Core (tar.gz)

2. Move the unziped file out to library
Use finder to find zip file, then unzip it.
If you can't find library directly, you can press shift + command + g, then input ~/Library.
Rename the file as tomcat.

3. Configration
Find a file named startup.sh in bin folder of tomcat folder, also you can see a file named shutdown.sh.
Enter Terminal, then drag the start file directly to the Terminal.
Then go to http://localhost:8080, if you can enter the website successful, that means it works.
If you want to close it, just close the Terminal or drag the close file to Terminal.
